docs.abstract: We asked veterans of political debates for their reviews of each of the Democratic hopefuls onstage Tuesday.
docs.snippet: We asked veterans of political debates for their reviews of each of the Democratic hopefuls onstage Tuesday.
docs.lead_paragraph: Before Tuesday’s Democratic primary debate, we asked political debate coaches and experts to tell us what each candidate needed to do to have a good night. Here’s that story. Today, we asked the experts how the candidates did.

headline.main: Which Candidates Won Last Night’s Democratic Debate? Six Experts Weigh In

byline.original: By Reid J. Epstein and Lisa Lerer

docs.abstract: Morgan Harper is challenging Representative Joyce Beatty in a solid blue Ohio district, the latest front in the Democratic clash between left and far left.
docs.snippet: Morgan Harper is challenging Representative Joyce Beatty in a solid blue Ohio district, the latest front in the Democratic clash between left and far left.
docs.lead_paragraph: COLUMBUS, Ohio — As Morgan Harper campaigned at the Prestige Cuts & Styles barbershop here, Joe Copeland, a retired school principal, said he had never heard of the young woman mounting an insurgent primary challenge of a Democratic member of Congress. But he thought of a comparison.

headline.main: The Democratic Debate Is Coming to Ohio, Where a Party Battle Is Already Underway
headline.print_headline: In Solid Blue Columbus District, a Clash Between the Left and the Far Left

docs.abstract: President Trump and his allies seized on debate moments over taxes, health care and economic inequality to portray the Democratic candidates as tax-and-spend liberals.
docs.snippet: President Trump and his allies seized on debate moments over taxes, health care and economic inequality to portray the Democratic candidates as tax-and-spend liberals.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump and his allies sought to turn the Democratic debate on Tuesday night into a referendum on the congressional impeachment inquiry, accusing the party’s presidential candidates and its leaders in Washington of pursuing a vendetta against Mr. Trump while ignoring more pressing pocketbook issues.

headline.main: Republicans, Defiant After Debate, Throw Punches on Impeachment and Economy
headline.print_headline: Republicans, Defiant After Debate, Throw Punches on Impeachment and Economy

docs.abstract: Mr. O’Rourke’s broad plan also seeks a path to citizenship for undocumented people and strengthened ties between the United States and Latin America.
docs.snippet: Mr. O’Rourke’s broad plan also seeks a path to citizenship for undocumented people and strengthened ties between the United States and Latin America.
docs.lead_paragraph: Beto O’Rourke released a broad immigration plan on Wednesday, pledging that as president he would immediately end several Trump administration border policies through executive action, offer protection from deportation to thousands of immigrants whose status in the United States is in limbo, and pass legislation that would create a pathway to citizenship for the 11 million immigrants in the country without permission.

headline.main: Beto O’Rourke Proposes Immigration Overhaul That Would Undo Trump Policies
headline.print_headline: O’Rourke Plan Would Undo Trump Border Policies

docs.abstract: Mr. Sanders’s climate change proposal calls for the United States to eliminate fossil fuel use by 2050. “We must be extraordinarily aggressive,” he said in an interview.
docs.snippet: Mr. Sanders’s climate change proposal calls for the United States to eliminate fossil fuel use by 2050. “We must be extraordinarily aggressive,” he said in an interview.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Bernie Sanders on Thursday released a $16.3 trillion blueprint to fight climate change, the latest and most expensive proposal from the field of Democratic presidential candidates aimed at reining in planet-warming greenhouse gases.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders’s ‘Green New Deal’: A $16 Trillion Climate Plan
headline.print_headline: Sanders Unveils Climate Change Plan, and Its $16 Trillion Price Tag

docs.abstract: Corey Lewandowski, President Trump’s former campaign manager, sounds a lot like his onetime boss as he weighs a run for Senate. Some Republican state leaders are shuddering.
docs.snippet: Corey Lewandowski, President Trump’s former campaign manager, sounds a lot like his onetime boss as he weighs a run for Senate. Some Republican state leaders are shuddering.
docs.lead_paragraph: WINDHAM, N.H. — As he called into Joe Piscopo’s radio show from a diner last week, and then trash-talked both political parties over a bacon-and-egg-white omelet, Corey Lewandowski demonstrated why he’d be a fitting Republican Senate nominee on the 2020 ticket with President Trump — and why that prospect appalls New Hampshire’s more traditional G.O.P. leaders.Mr. Lewandowski, the president’s former campaign manager, sounded every bit like his pugilistic political patron as he unleashed a blur of attacks and insinuations in a manner reminiscent of an out-of-control garden hose.

headline.main: Will Trumpism Take Deeper Root in New Hampshire?
headline.print_headline: Trump Lieutenant Unsettles New Hampshire Republicans

docs.abstract: Democratic presidential candidates recently spoke of the need to address the adverse effects of global warming on poor and marginalized communities.
docs.snippet: Democratic presidential candidates recently spoke of the need to address the adverse effects of global warming on poor and marginalized communities.
docs.lead_paragraph: The presidential candidates at the CNN climate forum on Wednesday repeatedly emphasized how climate change is hurting low-income communities and people of color, reflecting a growing awareness among Democrats that many of the problems they seek to address are inextricably tied to racism, poverty and other forms of discrimination and inequality.

headline.main: Environmental Justice Was a Climate Forum Theme. Here’s Why.

docs.abstract: Now fourth in the Democratic money chase and under fire from President Trump, Joseph R. Biden Jr. is increasingly dependent on his top donors, many of whom met in Philadelphia.
docs.snippet: Now fourth in the Democratic money chase and under fire from President Trump, Joseph R. Biden Jr. is increasingly dependent on his top donors, many of whom met in Philadelphia.
docs.lead_paragraph: PHILADELPHIA — Leading donors for Joseph R. Biden Jr. convened this weekend for their first donor retreat since he announced his candidacy and struck a determined posture as Mr. Biden’s campaign found itself under assault from President Trump, losing its clear front-runner status and lapped in the money chase by multiple Democratic rivals, most notably Senator Elizabeth Warren.

headline.main: Top Biden Donors Gather Amid Storm Clouds Over Campaign
headline.print_headline: With Biden Under Attack, Big-Money Donors Gather to Plot Fortifications

docs.abstract: Ms. Warren’s fund-raising total is likely to place her third among Democrats in the second quarter, behind Pete Buttigieg and Joseph R. Biden Jr.
docs.snippet: Ms. Warren’s fund-raising total is likely to place her third among Democrats in the second quarter, behind Pete Buttigieg and Joseph R. Biden Jr.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts raised $19.1 million in the past three months, her campaign said on Monday, a total that places her firmly in the top echelon of the Democratic money race and ahead of her main rival for the party’s progressive wing, Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren’s Fund-Raising: $19.1 Million in 3 Months, Outpacing Sanders
headline.print_headline: Warren Reports Raising $19.1 Million in 3 Months

byline.original: By Reid J. Epstein and Astead W. Herndon

docs.abstract: The Vermont senator’s wife said he is in good spirits and should be able to return home by the end of this coming weekend.
docs.snippet: The Vermont senator’s wife said he is in good spirits and should be able to return home by the end of this coming weekend.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders, recovering in a Las Vegas hospital from a procedure to treat a clogged artery, should be able to return home by the end of this weekend and will participate in the next Democratic debate, his wife, Jane Sanders, said Thursday.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders Will Participate in Next Debate, His Campaign Says
headline.print_headline: Sanders’s Campaign Says He Will Be Ready for Democrats’ Next Debate
